Sec. 19.008. APPLYING FOR FOUNDATION GROVE DESIGNATION, BUDWOOD
CERTIFICATION, AND CITRUS NURSERY CERTIFICATION. (a) A person who
desires to operate a foundation grove and produce certified citrus
budwood for sale to the citrus industry must apply for foundation
grove designation and citrus budwood certification in accordance with
rules adopted by the department.
(b) A person who desires to operate a citrus nursery to
propagate citrus nursery stock for sale in the citrus zone must apply
for citrus nursery certification in accordance with rules adopted by
the department.
Added by Acts 1995, 74th Leg., ch. 358, Sec. 1, eff. June 8, 1995.
Amended by:
Acts 2013, 83rd Leg., R.S., Ch. 166 (S.B. 1427), Sec. 7, eff.
September 1, 2013.

